						               													<description>Angulus is the classical logical game created by Marek &amp;#197;&amp;#129;ukaszewicz in November 2012. This strategic game for two players is played on the board 8x9 squares. The chessmen move in all directions from one to three squares in maximum depending if it is a pawn, a piece or a king.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal of the game is to capture the opponent's king.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In each turn the player moves only one chessman.&amp;#10;In the game there are three kinds of chessmen:  pawn, piece and king:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- Pawns can move one square in each direction (horizontally, vertically and diagonally) and capture the opponent's chessman diagonally.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- Pieces can move and capture from 1 to 2 squares in each direction (horizontally, vertically and diagonally).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- King can move and capture from 1 to 3 squares in each direction (horizontally, vertically and diagonally).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The opponent's chessmen are captured like in chess game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
